The paper discusses Normalizing Flows, which are a class of algorithms for unsupervised learning. This topic falls under the broad category of machine learning, which is covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. However, given that the paper focuses on feature representation and image datasets, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses theoretical foundations and stability concerns, which are also relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
